Got it — C: Pantheon mapping. Here’s the terrain model translated into Pantheon roles, with a clean “who does what” on each battlefield feature.

Pantheon Battlefield Geometry Map

The 5 terrain features
	•	Basins (local minima / sticky defaults)
	•	Saddles (tiny pivots that change access)
	•	Ridges (hard invariants / crypto + hardware)
	•	Canyons (high-gradient optimization channels)
	•	Lava Tubes (hidden unintended paths)

⸻

1) Basins — “Sticky defaults” and habitual failure modes

Threat: teams fall into convenience patterns (overbroad permissions, stale secrets, auto-approvals).

Pantheon roles
	•	Mother Duck (Ledger): baseline snapshots + weekly diff (“what drifted?”)
	•	Mirror (Policy): sets the default stance (deny-by-default, least privilege)
	•	Goblin Financier (Cost): prices the basin (“what does this convenience cost us later?”)
	•	Sisyphus (Clock): enforces repetition as discipline: recurring audits, not one-offs

Signature artifact: Basin Map
Top 10 defaults that create repeatable risk + the “resistance knobs” to unstick them.

⸻

2) Saddles — “Small actions that flip the game”

Examples: password reset, OAuth consent, “add collaborator,” support escalation, tool authorization.

Pantheon roles
	•	Hound (Detector): watches saddle attempts + anomaly patterns (velocity, geo, time, intent mismatch)
	•	Mirror (Verifier): step-up verification logic (“prove you’re you”)
	•	Checksum (Signer): anything irreversible needs a signed reason card
	•	The Man Blinking Slower Than Time (T=0 Governor): enforces delay on high-risk moves (anti-panic, anti-speed-run)
	•	Weasel Lawyer (Counsel): makes the rules legible; writes the escalation scripts and constraints

Signature artifact: Saddle Hardening Pack
A checklist of “step-up + rate limit + second channel + reason card” for every saddle.

⸻

3) Ridges — “Hard invariants that don’t negotiate”

Crypto, HSM/TPM, attestation, signed chains.

Threat: wasted energy trying to “talk past math.”

Pantheon roles
	•	Checksum (Integrity): the ridge itself — proof boundaries, signatures, hash chains
	•	Mirror (Discipline): prevents category error (“this is not a narrative layer”)
	•	Arctic Framework (Silence Machine): when you hit a ridge, output can be silence or refusal; preserve invariants
	•	Ghost Calculator: computes conditions (“we do not cross this ridge; route effort elsewhere”)

Signature artifact: Ridge Register
List of “non-negotiables” + what must never be attempted (and where the real leaks would occur instead: recovery paths, humans, configs).

⸻

4) Canyons — “High-gradient channels where everything flows downhill”

Optimization pressure creates predictable flows: speed culture, engagement KPIs, broad agent tool permissions.

Pantheon roles
	•	Prism Mosaic (Signal Weave): detects emergent high-flow channels across metrics/logs
	•	Hound (Tripwires): canyon sensors: error bursts, unusual tool use, action frequency
	•	Dragonfly (Remediation): safe interventions: throttle, degrade, sandbox, rotate tokens
	•	Hidden Ink Protocol v2.0: degrade ladder + reason codes + dual control planes when the canyon floods
	•	Cadence Master Daemon (Conductor): governs pacing; prevents “speed becomes policy”

Signature artifact: Canyon Dam Plan
Where to add friction: tool scopes, rate limits by action class, circuit breakers, kill switches, approval gates.

⸻

5) Lava Tubes — “Hidden paths nobody is watching”

Shadow IT, old debug endpoints, legacy creds, backdoors-by-accident.

Pantheon roles
	•	Hound (Scout): continuous discovery sweeps (inventory, endpoint mapping, permission diff)
	•	Mother Duck (Ledger): dependency manifests (Declare Inks) + attested inventories
	•	Mirror (Governance): “nothing ships without manifest” rule
	•	Checksum (Seal): signed manifests / provenance chains
	•	Goblin Financier: funds removal of tubes (“pay down the cave debt”)

Signature artifact: Lava Tube Census
An enumerated list of “unknown unknowns” converted into known, owned, and monitored surfaces.

⸻

The Pantheon “Field Manual” (How the team moves)

Core workflow
	1.	Hound detects terrain (anomaly / drift / tube).
	2.	Mirror classifies (basin/saddle/ridge/canyon/tube) + sets policy.
	3.	Ghost Calculator computes conditions + reversibility + option value.
	4.	Dragonfly executes bounded remediation (throttle, isolate, degrade).
	5.	Checksum signs the change + reason card.
	6.	Mother Duck logs it immutably; Sisyphus schedules recurrence.

This is the Shield Wall in action: interlocked roles, no single point of failure.

⸻

Pantheon “Entropy Gradient Doctrine” (one sentence)

Don’t fight ridges. Control gradients. Harden saddles. Dam canyons. Census lava tubes. Unstick basins.

⸻

